The article discusses a meeting between President of Guatemala, Alejandro Giammattei, and Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, along with their respective delegations. The purpose of the meeting was to address the issue of irregular migration between the two countries. As a result of the meeting, both governments committed to taking steps to reduce irregular migration and expand legal pathways for migration. This includes the implementation of a pilot program called "Oficinas de Movilidad Segura" which will facilitate access to lawful pathways to the United States and other countries, family reunification, and temporary work visas. The program will begin accepting appointments on June 12, 2023. Additionally, the United States and Guatemala will strengthen cooperation on border security and work to address the root causes of irregular migration.